  "text": "Most gel-based assays can also be assembled on glass coverslips or in glass bottom dishes and the behaviour of cells above, under, or within the gel (if the gel is transparent) can be observed continuously, using real time or time-lapse microscopy [CITATION_1] . Tracks of individual cells can be traced continuously and parameters such as velocity or the straightness of the path can be obtained.",
